# ðŸš€ ProofPoint

ProofPoint is a security and ownership-tracking platform that allows users to verify electronic goods via serial numbers, upload invoices, and report stolen items.  
This repository contains the backend setup for ProofPoint using **Node.js** and **PostgreSQL** in Docker.

---

## ðŸ“¦ Project Structure
- **Dockerfile** â†’ Builds the ProofPoint backend image.  
- **docker-compose.yml** â†’ Orchestrates the backend + PostgreSQL database.  
- **backend/** â†’ Node.js server code (entry: `backend/server.js`).  

---

## ðŸ›  Prerequisites
- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/)  
- [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)  
- GitHub account with access to GitHub Container Registry (for publishing images).  

---

## ðŸ”¨ Build & Run (Local)

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/proofpoint.git
cd proofpoint
docker build -t proofpoint-backend .
docker-compose up
docker images | grep proofpoint
docker logs <container_id>
version: "3.9"
services:
  proofpoint:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    depends_on:
      - postgres

  postgres:
    image: postgres:15
    restart: always
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: proofpoint
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: secretpassword
      POSTGRES_DB: proofpointdb
    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data

volumes:
  postgres_data:

---


